HEADWORD: Cadaster
<hw>Ca*das"ter</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>cadastre</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law.)</fld> <def>An official statement of the quantity and value
of real estate for the purpose of apportioning the taxes payable on such
property; a public register showing the details of ownership and value
of land.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

